          <exercise label="gas-price">
            <title>Reasoning proportionally and convert between units</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The cost of a liter of gasoline in Brasilia in June 2023 was 5.23 Brazilian
                    Real. Convert 5.23 Real/liter to US dollars/gallon. Use the exchange rate 
                    1 B Real = 0.21 US Dollar and the conversion factor 1 liter = 0.264 gallon in 
                    your work. Round to the nearest penny per gallon.
                </p>
                <p>The equivalent cost is <var /> US $ per gallon.</p>
            </statement>
            <setup>
                <var>
                    <condition number="4.16" tolerance="0.01">
                        <feedback>
                            <p>
                                Correct.
                            </p>
                        </feedback>
                    </condition>
                    <condition string="*.*">
                        <feedback>
                            <p>
                                Incorrect. 
                            </p>
                        </feedback>
                    </condition>
                </var>
            </setup>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    How do we define being able to do this problem? Speed is less important that reasoning 
                    it out. Can you set it up and use your knowledge of multiplication and division of fractions? 
                    Searching for similar problems to mimic or looking at the 
                    solution does not count as knowledge of the topic.
                </p>
            </hint>
            <answer>
            <p>
                4.16 US dollars per gallon
            </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
            <p>
                <m>\frac{5.23 \text{BRL}}{1 \text{liter}}\cdot\frac{0.21 \text{USD}}{1\text{BRL}}
                    \cdot\frac{1 \text{liter}}{0.264\text{gal}}</m>
            </p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <title>Understanding and using percentages</title>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Write <m>64\%</m> as a simplified fraction.
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <!--<answer>
                    <p>
                        <m>\frac{16}{25}</m>
                    </p>
                </answer> -->
            </task> 
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        If you take a 5 percent cut in pay this year and then get 
                        a 10 percent raise 
                        the following year, by what percent will your salary grow over the 
                        two-year period?  
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <choices>
                    <choice>
                        <p> 2.5 percent
                        </p>
                    </choice>
                    <choice correct="yes"> 
                        <p>
                            4.5 percent  
                        </p>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <p> 5 percent
                        </p>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <p> 7.5 percent
                        </p>
                    </choice>
                </choices>
                <!--</answer>
                    <p> 4.5 percent </p>
                </answer>-->
            </task>  
            <task> 
                <statement>
                        
                    <p> Your restaurant bill of $55.59 includes a 
                        9% meals tax. What was the charge for the meal 
                        before the tax was added? Your answer should be  
                        correct to the nearest cent.
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <answer>
                    <p>
                        $51.00. If you got $50.59, you made the common 
                            mistake of subtracting <m>0.9\cdot 55.59</m> from 
                            $55.59. Check your work by increasing your answer by 
                            9 percent. Do you get $55.59? 
                    </p>
                </answer>
            </task>
