    <conclusion>
        <p component="nursing">
            If you are unable to do the above problems on your own, 
            you should decide whether MA100 <xref ref="ch-MR"/> or 
            MA123 Quantitative Literacy is the appropriate course for you. Choose
            MA100 Math Refresher only if you need to develop skills in working with
            fractions, simplifying expressions, and solving linear equations. If you take MA100, 
            you will have no electives in your nursing degree plan. Some of the skills 
            will be briefly reviewed in MA123, but with less depth and a faster pace 
            than in MA100. 
    </p>
    <p component="nursing">
        If you are a nursing major and almost all the above problems seem easy for 
        you, you might not be required to take a mathematics course and could be eligible 
        to take a free elective instead. 
        Since you will need to do similar problems in your nursing courses and
        licensure exams, this waiver is only granted for students with exceptionally strong 
        math backgrounds.  Your 
        advisor and the mathematics program director will review your 
        request for a waiver of the mathematics requirement. If you change your major later, 
        you will need to fulfill the mathematics requirement to graduate.           
    </p>
